      "message": "I think actually all the vars here: https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/luci/client/libs/logdog/bootstrap.py?type\u003dcs\u0026q\u003dLOGDOG_STREAM_SERVER_PATH\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026g\u003d0\u0026l\u003d30\n\n    LOGDOG_STREAM_PROJECT - The LUCI project \n    LOGDOG_STREAM_PREFIX  - The prefix of the logging session (before the \u0027+\u0027)\n    LOGDOG_STREAM_SERVER_PATH - The local path/socket/etc. to the local butler service\n    LOGDOG_COORDINATOR_HOST - The hostname of the logdog coordinator, used to compose URLs\n    LOGDOG_NAMESPACE - The prefix of the logdog stream name.\n\n\nedit - or did you omit these others because they\u0027re not strictly required for the protocol?",
